Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.07,0:00:08.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, Tanabe, how are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.61,0:00:12.79,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They still have us doing training cruises between the Earth and the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.61,0:00:16.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it's been six months since we passed the selection tests...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.31,0:00:19.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we're about to set out on a long haul of seven years, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.12,0:00:22.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I shouldn't be surprised that preparing for it is taking a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.65,0:00:27.79,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and you don't need to worry so much.\NOur teamwork is pretty much perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.36,0:00:29.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I think we're all getting along pretty well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.55,0:00:33.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, except for a certain middle-aged troublemaker...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.01,0:00:37.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're starting another round of shipboard testing tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.57,0:00:39.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...so it'll be a week before I can mail you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.07,0:00:41.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,See you. Hang in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.01,0:00:43.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and say hi to Pritch for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.58,0:00:48.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Dear Senpai. You should try to get along with your father better.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.91,0:00:52.60,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Use the seven years to make up for lost time and become closer as father and son.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.62,0:00:56.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As for me, I'm doing rehab exercises all day, every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.59,0:00:59.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have that to thank for my steady recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.56,0:01:02.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The doctors complimented me, saying I was doing really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.79,0:01:05.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've been asking them to let me go back into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.40,0:01:09.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and they say that if I keep it up, they should be able to give me the okay by next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.84,0:01:12.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, if I do,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.14,0:01:15.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,can we meet up there in space?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.43,0:02:53.36,F.O. (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(538,368,375,355)\fad(760,830)\bord0.1\shad2\fs20\fscx100\fscy100\t(\fs26\fscx100\fscy100)}And The Days We Chance Upon...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.54,0:03:01.92,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Due to the political prisoners and serious criminals housed in this facility, special security measures are in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.75,0:03:03.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.29,0:03:06.86,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Be advised that entry by unauthorized persons...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.08,0:03:05.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's it been, a year?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.23,0:03:06.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.87,0:03:09.65,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...or parties unaffiliated with this facility is not allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.41,0:03:08.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That long, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.16,0:03:12.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Cheng-Shin, l...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.14,0:03:12.75,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.13,0:03:13.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, let me go first.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.91,0:03:16.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How come? I started talking first, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.99,0:03:19.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When something like this needs to be said, the younger person goes first.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.56,0:03:23.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Only by a couple of months! Besides, don't you mean it should be the older person?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.00,0:03:23.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What's going on out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.23,0:03:26.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In my family, the younger person always goes first.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.27,0:03:26.00,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Nothing, ma'am. Looks like a simple squabble.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.22,0:03:29.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Like I care about that. Anyway, I was the one who started talking first.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.44,0:03:28.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I wish they'd pick a more suitable place for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.56,0:03:29.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That's for sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.89,0:03:31.11,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So you'd better listen good!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.50,0:03:33.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll listen to what you have to say after you get back from Jupiter, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.06,0:03:39.03,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Regular check of point 3-0-3 complete.\NOfficers in charge, take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.52,0:03:36.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can go first then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.20,0:03:38.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.20,0:03:41.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you come back, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.09,0:03:42.53,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.19,0:03:44.37,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.22,0:03:48.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, we're the people who submitted that visitation request form the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.17,0:04:00.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take a seat, Claire Rondo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.37,0:04:01.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.85,0:04:19.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are you two doing here?\NVisiting hours will end soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.69,0:04:24.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To tell you the truth, I'd planned to come see you sooner. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.63,0:04:27.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. It's not easy to get permission to visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.30,0:04:30.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi, you used your pull as a crew member, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.85,0:04:33.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah, sorta...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.70,0:04:37.00,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's ironic, isn't it? I have the Von Braun to thank for being able to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.87,0:04:38.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear the verdict?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.24,0:04:42.11,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Ten years was a bit much, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.42,0:04:45.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For one thing, the Von Braun didn't crash...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.42,0:04:49.14,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For a terrorist, it's a light sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.75,0:04:51.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was because I told them everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.96,0:04:53.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It just means that I was a small potatoes to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.19,0:04:56.13,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But Fee-san and the others didn't say anything, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.70,0:04:58.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You could've denied that you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.40,0:05:02.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I needed it. I felt like I deserved to be punished.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.03,0:05:07.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to become a member of society.\NTo be recognized as a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.94,0:05:10.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to believe that I deserved to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.81,0:05:14.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I worked so hard at Technora.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.85,0:05:18.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But it's like I said to you, Hachi.\NI couldn't keep up with a thoroughbred.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.64,0:05:19.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.05,0:05:22.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I pushed myself too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.76,0:05:25.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Before I knew it, I couldn't tell what was what anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.74,0:05:31.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When Tanabe-san and I crashed on the moon,\NI thought to myself, "I'm going to die here."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.70,0:05:34.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I would've been better off if I'd been killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.94,0:05:37.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.81,0:05:48.79,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, she didn't abandon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.57,0:05:52.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If she had used my oxygen, she could easily have saved herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.16,0:06:03.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Her O   usage was higher than mine because she was carrying me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.16,0:06:03.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(205,453)\fs20}2
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.73,0:06:10.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right when I was thinking of taking off my helmet and getting it over with,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.74,0:06:13.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...that's when I saw the shuttle bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.64,0:06:22.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't looking to be rescued.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.01,0:06:24.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.33,0:06:27.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't bring myself to abandon her, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.62,0:06:30.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.92,0:06:32.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Because you liked her?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.53,0:06:36.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not likely. I couldn't stand her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.26,0:06:39.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She goes on and on about things she doesn't know anything about...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.70,0:06:41.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and thinks that everything can be sorted out if you only try hard enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.40,0:06:44.98,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When I was sent to Debris Section and had to work under her, l...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.02,0:06:49.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When people make you angry or sad,\N it's because you care about what they think.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.87,0:06:53.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The opposite of love isn't hate, it's apathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.28,0:06:56.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you didn't care what they thought, you wouldn't hate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.65,0:07:00.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.38,0:07:02.60,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.95,0:07:04.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it was like you were saying,\N"Don't you dare die on me!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.93,0:07:07.50,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you get that from?\N Your reasoning isn't really connected there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.83,0:07:12.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, exactly! A while ago, I had this revelation about what space is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.03,0:07:15.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I realized that everything in it is connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.03,0:07:16.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's connected?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.47,0:07:20.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Somewhere deep down, you and Tanabe are connected, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.50,0:07:21.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just people, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.17,0:07:25.12,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're probably connected to that shuttle bus that was passing by. And to El Tanika, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.43,0:07:27.41,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then you and I are connected?\NAnd Claire, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.72,0:07:28.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.61,0:07:31.17,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like you've turned into a philosopher.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.44,0:07:32.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make fun of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.09,0:07:36.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Claire, I'll be able to make it to Jupiter because I realized that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.82,0:07:41.19,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well... Maybe you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.46,0:07:43.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.71,0:07:44.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,El Tanikan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.33,0:07:51.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Once I've served my sentence, I was thinking of translating first-world books into El Tanikan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.74,0:07:54.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Because the thing that El Tanika needs most of all to rebuild is education.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.69,0:07:55.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You are, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.97,0:08:01.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Because I can't keep\N my promise to Temara-san now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.05,0:08:06.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't keep it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.08,0:08:07.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.69,0:08:11.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's because I still want to be connected to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.01,0:08:14.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You do, huh?\NHang in there, Claire.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.90,0:08:15.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.82,0:08:17.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What was that word that you wrote just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.03,0:08:19.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Miig."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.51,0:08:23.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It means, "Thank you, see you again soon."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.20,0:08:27.86,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hello there. Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.47,0:08:31.14,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The board has just reached a consensus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.61,0:08:35.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've decided to reinstate you at Technora, Dolf-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.06,0:08:40.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We place a high value on those skills of yours that kept the Jupiter project on track.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.95,0:08:43.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than returning you to your old job of division director,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.37,0:08:46.00,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...we've prepared a VP post for you at the head office.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.48,0:08:48.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We want you to oversee our new Solar System Development project...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.83,0:08:51.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When I was transferred from Second Division to Galileo Development, I was told...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.10,0:08:56.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...it was a promotion because my title was changing from director to company president.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.77,0:08:59.19,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This time, I'm going from company president to vice president,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.95,0:09:01.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...so doesn't that make this a demotion?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.19,0:09:04.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Spare us the sarcasm, Dolf-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.68,0:09:06.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be a VP of Technora, a worldwide company.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.11,0:09:09.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Being president of a little company like Galileo\NDevelopment is nothing in comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.03,0:09:14.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll admit that there is no comparison between the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.36,0:09:11.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose not.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.79,0:09:17.82,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who could possibly need to ask if it would be better to be a pet dog or a lone wolf?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.33,0:09:25.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Galileo Development is going independent?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.56,0:09:29.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,President Dolf turned them down when they offered to send him back to Technora.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.03,0:09:32.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's because it looks like the\NJupiter project will succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.04,0:09:34.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If they thought it would fail, they would cut him loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.08,0:09:37.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If it looked to be successful, they would return him to Technora.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.24,0:09:40.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like that was what they had in mind at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.78,0:09:42.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? But what about...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.76,0:09:44.73,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Down, boy! Hands off! This has onions in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.46,0:09:47.04,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what're you doing! Down, boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.88,0:09:46.41,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hands off that, too! For other reasons!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.63,0:09:53.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Getting back to what I was saying, is it a good idea to pick a fight with the head office?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.52,0:09:56.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's secured Dr. Locksmith's backing and now has a monopoly on his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.09,0:09:59.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If Technora doesn't want to fall behind in the space development race,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.30,0:10:02.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...I suppose they will have no choice but to play ball with President Dolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.47,0:10:04.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, he told them that he'd gone to\NVega and struck a deal with them first.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.71,0:10:07.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Remember, they're the ones who'd been removed from the Jupiter project.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.21,0:10:10.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Wow, it was a premeditated crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.41,0:10:13.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Did I say something funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.64,0:10:27.03,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,McCoy-sama of the Irving funeral, please return to the reception center.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.07,0:10:29.73,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've got one last lesson to teach you.\NIt's very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.53,0:10:32.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Every ship needs a harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.65,0:10:34.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They need a harbor that will always be there waiting for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.25,0:10:38.85,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and will take them in when they finally arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.24,0:10:40.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.80,0:10:44.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, give my best to Goro.\NWe'd both get all maudlin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.61,0:10:45.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I want you two to try to get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.88,0:10:48.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That old meddler.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.40,0:10:53.37,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Doors to the lunar pioneer joint memorial service will be closed at 5PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.27,0:10:52.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't need to worry.\N You and me, we're best buddies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.89,0:10:54.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we sure are, Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.59,0:10:57.11,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say something weird just now, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.04,0:10:57.82,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Those planning to attend, please make a note of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.20,0:10:59.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But you're the one who said we're bestest buddies, Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.52,0:11:01.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't call me that, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.03,0:11:04.53,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just call me "Dad," you hear?\NIt's just "Dad."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.77,0:11:05.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.66,0:11:11.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Gigalt. We won't be visiting you again for seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.54,0:11:14.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, I'll take a picture of Jupiter for you with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.67,0:11:18.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, what're you gonna do now?\NYou still have some vacation time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.58,0:11:19.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna stop by Seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.65,0:11:20.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's the point of going there now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.38,0:11:22.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause Tanabe says she's coming into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.12,0:11:25.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She is, huh? She's well enough to go into space already?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.90,0:11:28.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she's been working hard down on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.01,0:11:59.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, you found me...\NAre you from the hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.82,0:12:03.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? My transmitter's not turned on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.55,0:12:05.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, I can hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.86,0:12:08.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um, could you keep this a secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.39,0:12:09.81,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.36,0:12:11.04,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.61,0:12:13.53,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Say, what're you doing out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.80,0:12:16.50,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm cleaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.00,0:12:21.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's a place that everyone's sullied, and I'm going to make it pristine again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.83,0:12:33.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Space has become a world that is monopolized by a handful of countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.18,0:12:37.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We should fix that, shouldn't we?\N We should start over from scratch, shouldn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.32,0:12:41.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And return all the countries to the way they should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.88,0:12:45.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Countries? Oh, I learned all about those.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.50,0:12:47.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Earth is divided up into those, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.07,0:12:51.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm a Lunarian!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.36,0:12:54.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was born and raised here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.52,0:12:56.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So I've never seen any of those\N"country" things myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.55,0:13:01.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, where's your country on Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.18,0:13:06.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Can you see it from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.32,0:13:12.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.01,0:13:16.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can't see any of them from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.40,0:13:19.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But I still...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.70,0:13:22.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can't see them from here, but I still...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.71,0:13:35.50,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now opening 5th Bay access.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.23,0:13:37.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oops! I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.40,0:13:41.01,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Weightless conditions are maintained within the station's port area,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.03,0:13:44.43,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...so we ask that all our visitors exercise caution while passing through.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.61,0:13:45.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.65,0:13:49.97,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Weightless conditions are maintained within the station's port area,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.32,0:13:46.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.79,0:13:50.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, Senpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.05,0:13:53.46,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...so we ask that all our visitors exercise caution while passing through.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.35,0:13:52.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I got myself a makeover.\NNice, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.12,0:13:55.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, that isn't very flattering on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.87,0:13:58.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You think so? I think it makes me look like a playboy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.20,0:13:59.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What're you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.48,0:14:01.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, how about a compliment at least?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.71,0:14:05.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hurry up and get those containers opened!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.94,0:14:07.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right! Sorry about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.95,0:14:12.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Back on the moon, I ran into Cheng-Shin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.95,0:14:15.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And I heard about what happened between you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.12,0:14:20.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So then I... I decked him.\NGood and hard with a fist like a rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.42,0:14:21.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You should've used scissors.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.38,0:14:23.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To poke his eyes out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.58,0:14:26.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, not that. A "V" peace sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.27,0:14:27.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that kind of scissors.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.47,0:14:30.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's just think of what you did as an example of tough love.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.76,0:14:32.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're okay with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.08,0:14:34.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, there are lots of kinds of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.31,0:14:37.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.68,0:14:42.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.84,0:14:45.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe? Are your legs okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.85,0:14:47.12,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Good as new.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.27,0:14:49.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, this place never changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.69,0:14:50.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.24,0:14:52.82,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.84,0:14:54.14,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.14,0:14:55.79,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you retired...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.05,0:14:57.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.62,0:15:00.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Starting this year, the retirement age has been pushed back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.11,0:15:00.50,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.72,0:15:05.12,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's true! When I told my wife, she said to work until I die!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.13,0:15:07.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, in a case like this, are you supposed to congratulate the person?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.93,0:15:08.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Probably not...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.98,0:15:10.85,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It is good to see the two of you back at the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.34,0:15:14.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri, neither one of us works for Technora anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.81,0:15:18.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's good to be back, Yuri-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.92,0:15:21.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like Keith-san's tip was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.85,0:15:22.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That you, Edel?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.07,0:15:24.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, does this mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.75,0:15:28.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When my contract came up for renewal,\NI was hired as a regular employee.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.74,0:15:30.98,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I work in General Affairs Section now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.34,0:15:32.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations, Edel!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.96,0:15:34.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. Here, this is for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.30,0:15:35.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.26,0:15:38.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A going-away present. It's a limited-edition item given out to stockholders.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.36,0:15:39.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.54,0:15:42.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, you wanna come with me to Jupiter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.08,0:15:46.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.78,0:15:49.81,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. These inflate to 20 meters in height.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.07,0:15:51.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,M-Make it stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.16,0:15:58.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that reminds me, Hachi!\NI made it big, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.27,0:16:00.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not an assistant anymore!\NI'm not an...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.93,0:16:02.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edel, make it stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.72,0:16:03.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.23,0:16:07.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, that scared me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.76,0:16:09.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,See, didn't I tell you that he was here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.94,0:16:11.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey there, celebrity!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.74,0:16:14.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you pay back all the money\NI lent you before you leave for Jupiter!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.53,0:16:16.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What're you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.06,0:16:17.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Tanabe!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.24,0:16:19.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's good to be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.02,0:16:20.00,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When did you get back?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.00,0:16:21.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You should've told us you were coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.62,0:16:24.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I wasn't even sure if\NI'd get permission to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.85,0:16:28.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, how's it going? Are things going well between you and the celebrity?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.24,0:16:31.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I guess. Speaking of which, Lucie, how are things with you and Colin?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.94,0:16:35.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Making steady progress!\NHe's gaga over me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.71,0:16:36.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, whatever...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.49,0:16:39.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Man, this is pretty amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.83,0:16:42.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he's really gonna get his own spaceship.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.58,0:16:44.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So pay us back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.07,0:16:46.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Von Braun isn't my personal property!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.24,0:16:47.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to you, you think you're so big!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.03,0:16:48.47,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Could I have your autograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.84,0:16:49.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sign this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.87,0:16:51.04,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's right! An autograph!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.37,0:16:54.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ha-chan, could you put your autograph and a message on that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.44,0:16:55.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not you, too, Chief...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.21,0:17:00.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Could you? Please? Please? We already have your picture there and everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.99,0:17:02.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's his will...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.44,0:17:05.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Write, "To my good friends at Debris Section"!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.69,0:17:07.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're a coworker who made it big, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.58,0:17:08.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.95,0:17:09.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.44,0:17:10.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stop embarrassing me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.09,0:17:13.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And anyway, that's my last will!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.06,0:17:14.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But you said that you didn't need it anymore, Ha-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.92,0:17:16.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's been in the company newsletter!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.21,0:17:18.17,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice that this will go down in history, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.17,0:17:19.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No it's not!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.16,0:17:32.55,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,DS-12, this is Seven.\NEstablishing datalink via Navstar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.69,0:17:34.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Datalink confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.98,0:17:38.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We will be making orbital plane change using ME to reach transfer orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.48,0:17:40.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...so we will separate using OMS until we reach changeover point.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.99,0:17:43.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Please verify vector and window datalinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.70,0:17:43.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We actually managed to get on board...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.14,0:17:45.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It was nice of Keith and the guys to make the arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.74,0:17:50.85,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,DS-12, this is Seven. Downlinking vector and window to navigation matrix complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.03,0:17:51.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. But when I hear Fee-san giving instructions,\NI get the sudden urge to go to the airlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.30,0:17:52.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, why don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.77,0:17:53.13,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.90,0:17:58.00,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We obviously can't let you collect debris, but\NI think it'd be okay if we let you go outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.41,0:17:59.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You two haven't put on any weight, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.15,0:18:02.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We have two suits in your old sizes waiting for you by the airlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.97,0:18:04.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can head out whenever you're ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.87,0:18:05.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You copy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.22,0:18:09.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I copy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.39,0:18:14.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,State vector, update.\NTransfer into polar orbit complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.23,0:18:17.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please monitor spaceworthiness test flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.52,0:18:21.02,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,DS-12, this is Seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.74,0:18:21.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your legs okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.46,0:18:22.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, they're fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.81,0:18:25.53,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Transfer into orbit\NZulu 1246, 52, 37 confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.54,0:18:26.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.67,0:18:27.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've seen this hundreds of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.43,0:18:32.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's true, but the first time I saw the\NEarth from space, it was really exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.45,0:18:36.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But when I look at the Earth after everything I've experienced,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.35,0:18:38.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...it moves me, but in a different way, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.51,0:18:39.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I think I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.89,0:18:45.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The aurora's so pretty...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.98,0:18:53.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, I want to come up here again.\NAs a debris hauler.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.13,0:18:56.82,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You will. I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.33,0:19:00.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you suppose those two are talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.16,0:19:03.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't do that, Chief.\NIt's not nice to eavesdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.07,0:19:05.86,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe, but as their former superiors,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.86,0:19:08.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...it's our duty to keep those youngsters under close supervision.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.27,0:19:11.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Duty? Well, if it's our duty, then we have no choice but to listen in!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.22,0:19:15.41,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You copy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.68,0:19:17.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I-I copy...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.81,0:19:19.13,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That was a very bad thing you did, Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.59,0:19:20.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.86,0:19:24.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs20\fad(200,200)\an7}NOTE: They are playing shiritori, a word game where the players\Nhave to say a word which begins with the final kana of the\Nprevious word.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.86,0:19:24.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ke. Kessuraaa shindoromu.\N(Kessler Syndrome)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.71,0:19:27.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mu... Mujuuryou-you jiku-uke.\N(Zero-G ball bearing)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.59,0:19:28.37,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Keresu.\N(Ceres)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.87,0:19:31.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Su? Su... Spin-nuke.\N(Spin release)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.92,0:19:34.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ke... Keiki hikou.\N(Instrument flight)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.60,0:19:35.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Uindou ake.\N(Window opener)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.05,0:19:38.00,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Kenedii uchuu sentaa.\N(Kennedy Space Center)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.26,0:19:39.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A? A, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.76,0:19:40.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.69,0:19:41.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ananke!\N (Jupiter's moon)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.03,0:19:45.41,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ke... Ke... Kenban haamonika.\N(Keyboard harmonica)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.74,0:19:46.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Kami no ke.\N(Hair)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.70,0:19:48.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, what's with all the "ke" words?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.92,0:19:49.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can't think of any more, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.49,0:19:51.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ke, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.45,0:19:58.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've got one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.06,0:20:00.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Kekkon shiyou.\N(Marry me)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.07,0:20:02.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's "u" to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.75,0:20:07.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.66,0:20:09.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha! You lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.78,0:22:31.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you're Kyutaro, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.22,0:22:34.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How does it feel to have two members of your family going to Jupiter?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.58,0:22:36.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have anything to say to your father and brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.54,0:22:40.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care about any of that.\NC'mon, get out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.30,0:22:42.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, don't be like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.16,0:22:45.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Clear the road! Clear the road, people!\NStick to the agreement!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.81,0:22:47.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you there! Move back!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.96,0:22:51.00,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Asking the family members of the crew personal questions is prohibited!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.14,0:22:50.50,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Goodness, what a ruckus...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.53,0:22:54.73,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who breaks the agreement will have their news permits revoked!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.75,0:22:52.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.72,0:22:55.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home.\NSounds pretty bad out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.60,0:22:58.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We told those guys that we aren't giving any interviews, so what the hell are they thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.27,0:23:01.82,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't born yet at the time, so you wouldn't remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.18,0:23:04.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but it was exactly the same when your father went to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.32,0:23:11.81,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The crew has just appeared in the access bay of the ship's centrifugal gravity block!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.74,0:23:10.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's already started!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.77,0:23:13.50,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ai-san? Hey, Ai-san! It's starting!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.39,0:23:15.11,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can see Captain Reny and Commander Weher!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.92,0:23:15.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, just a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.61,0:23:17.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, I said that I'll take care of that stuff for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.32,0:23:17.58,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Following them are the chosen elite!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.96,0:23:19.53,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, I can handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.96,0:23:21.55,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,These men and women who will be aboard mankind's first manned mission to Jupiter...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.80,0:23:21.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's right, you're worrying too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.69,0:23:23.76,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...truly have the right stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.88,0:23:22.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who asked you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.27,0:23:24.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, sit here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.63,0:23:30.61,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Each small step they take could rightly be said to be a new step in the development of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.77,0:23:25.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.59,0:23:26.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You, too, Mom! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.13,0:23:30.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to you, you're more worked up than anyone else here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.18,0:23:32.51,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And then we turn to the Von Braun,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.86,0:23:34.80,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...which has met with her fair share of tragedy while undergoing testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.18,0:23:38.85,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,From this day forward, the name of this ship, the culmination of all mankind's knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.23,0:23:38.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.48,0:23:43.54,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...will go down in the history books as the ark that carried these great men and women.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.49,0:23:42.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look at Hachirota-san, he's so nervous...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.15,0:23:47.14,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um, what just happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.41,0:23:51.49,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Chief Engineer Hoshino seems to have done something to his son, Astronaut Hachirota.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.79,0:23:54.28,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my! The Chief Engineer has just been grabbed by his son!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.30,0:23:56.86,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, this is an international broadcast!\NThey're embarrassing us!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.29,0:23:57.82,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Astronaut Hachirota Hoshino, a Japanese national,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.99,0:23:58.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine. They're always like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.04,0:24:02.01,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...is an extravehicular activity specialist, also known as EVA, aboard the Von Braun.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.04,0:24:02.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But this is Jupiter we're talking about!\NCome in and watch, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.02,0:24:05.51,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As representatives of our country, we look forward to witnessing...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.12,0:24:03.12,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Once I get these hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.15,0:24:05.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The damn laundry can wait until tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.91,0:24:10.31,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...the great exploits of this man and his father, an engineer of unsurpassed skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.72,0:24:10.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Geez... I guess being the wife of a guy like\NDad means putting up with stunts like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.01,0:24:14.66,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This fearless, frank attitude that they display in the face of this magnum opus of humanity...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.42,0:24:13.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.68,0:24:18.12,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's a little late, but are you sure you should let him leave like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.01,0:24:18.13,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...gives us confidence in that this mission will end in success.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.58,0:24:23.02,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For this occasion, the crew will form a line, and pictures will be taken by the press corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.22,0:24:22.19,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mom and Dad are one thing, but you and Hachi are newlyweds, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.67,0:24:23.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.99,0:24:27.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna be apart for seven whole years. And besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.98,0:24:28.65,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Although relaxed, some tension remains, and we can see that the entire crew...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.97,0:24:28.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Besides?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.02,0:24:32.11,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...is looking forward to their departure, now mere hours away.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.09,0:24:32.11,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what if there's an accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.47,0:24:35.73,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The distance from Earth to Jupiter is some 800 million kilometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.05,0:24:38.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be fine. He gave me his word.\NHe promised that he'd come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.91,0:24:40.01,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It is as if these men and women are diving into the sky even now,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.54,0:24:42.68,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...diving into the vast, mind-boggling depths of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.33,0:24:42.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't get you guys...
